Rating: 3
Great base recipe!! I used andouille sausage which gave the recipe a spicy kick. I pureed half of the sausage with the rest of the ingredients and added the other half back to the puree. Throughout the cooking process I did add additional water as well as a cup of mashed potatoes and about 1/2 cup sour cream. I also used the gouda as a garnish and did not make the gouda toasts. It was a hit!

Rating: 4
Made a variation of this for a Pea Soup contest in my family. I despise pea soup with a passion, but liked this one! I wish I would have known to / thought of: 1) Clean the sausage out of the soup before cutting. It makes much nicer bits, especially for the croutons. 2) If I am to ever make this again, I will cut the sausage to half and I will not return the sausage after purée. I would serve them on top of the soup and perhaps have a bowl of cut sausage for those who prefer more. One comment was made that it was ''ham soup''. After reading the comments, I chose to: Purée the soup to make it more potage and higher end tasting. I also added coloured carrots 30 minutes in.

