Rating: 4
My family loves this soup. Very creamy and tasty. I use half green and half yellow split peas.I also cook an additional kielbasa with chicken broth in another pot (so the soup does not get to salty) being my family loves the sausage. I have made this soup about 6 times and will continue. It is a keeper.

Rating: 4
Wow! This was the perfect meal on a wintery cold January night. I used slightly more peas (20 oz) and less kielbasa (14 oz) simply because of the package sizes. The additional peas and an extra half hour of cooking resulted in a lovely thick puree. I read comments that some were underwhelmed by the toast, and with a small change, it was perfect to my taste. On lightly toasted sourdough slices, spread some spicy mustard, then a slice of tomato, with salt and freshly ground pepper. As I used all the kielbasa in the soup, I put only grated Gouda on top of the tomato slice and put under the broiler until the cheese melted. The tomato made a nice tangy contrast to the smooth pea soup. My husband loved the toasts so much he suggested that we make them as an hors d'oeuvre for company. I'm sure we will have this dish frequently.

